(T.J.): Best not to. The skin will be rubbery, and it will prolly cook unevenly. It

just won't taste good. Better to bake them uncovered in a 350F oven for 30

mins or so until the juices run clear when pricked by a fuel. To get a nice

brown skin,. season with salt and pepper, baste with butter or oil. Internal

temp near the vine should be 170F

